author: a Baltimore Sun reporter
title: Navy quarterback Keenan Reynolds vying for Johnny Unitas Golden Arm Award
text:
Navy quarterback Keenan Reynolds vying for Johnny Unitas Golden Arm Award Navy quarterback Keenan Reynolds 
Navy quarterback Keenan Reynolds is vying for the 2015 Johnny Unitas Golden Arm Award. 
Navy quarterback Keenan Reynolds is vying for the 2015 Johnny Unitas Golden Arm Award. (Rob Carr / Getty Images) a Baltimore Sun reporter Which local quarterback is vying for the Unitas Golden Arm award? 
Navy quarterback Keenan Reynolds is among 15 quarterbacks vying for the 2015 Johnny Unitas Golden Arm Award after the field was cut in half this week. 
The Top 30 Watch List has been trimmed to the following candidates, in addition to Reynolds: Trevone Boykin, TCU; Jacoby Brissett, N.C. State; Connor Cook, Michigan State; Brandon Doughty, Western Kentucky; Everett Golson, Florida State; Kevin Hogan, Stanford; Matt Johnson, Bowling Green; Cody Kessler, USC; Paxton Lynch, Memphis; Dak Prescott, Mississippi State; Nate Sudfeld, Indiana; Carson Wentz, N. Dakota State; Marquise Williams, North Carolina; and Travis Wilson, Utah. 
Named after the former Baltimore Colts quarterback and established in 1987, this award is presented at the end of each season to the nation’s top college quarterback. Candidates must be a college senior or fourth-year junior on schedule to graduate with their class. 
The award will be presented Dec. 11 in Baltimore. Last year’s winner was Heisman Trophy winner Marcus Mariota of Oregon.
